1
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:50,200
Freeze! Stop right there!

2
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:52,800
Stay where you are!
Move again, and I'll shoot!

3
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:54,280
Don't shoot! Please!

4
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:55,920
We surrender!

5
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,360
‪My goodness.

6
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:04,840
DIE

7
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:24,960
What are you laughing at?

8
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:26,560
Enjoy the foot-soaking water?

9
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:43,640
Officer He. We…

10
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:45,720
- We met before.
- We met before.

11
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:48,160
Do I know you? Did I arrest you before?

12
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:50,080
- Yesterday afternoon. Yesterday afternoon.
- Afternoon.

13
00:02:50,160 --> 00:02:52,040
- I just saw you.
- We met.

14
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,640
TRANSFORM BUSINESS FOR GROWTH

15
00:02:58,720 --> 00:02:59,920
You work for Jin Manshan?

16
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:02,240
Then why didn't you
tell the truth yesterday?

17
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:04,320
Are you involved
with the missing father and daughter?

18
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:06,040
Nothing to do with us!

19
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:08,120
- We just came here to take a look.
- We are just…

20
00:03:08,200 --> 00:03:08,880
What does that have to do with anything?

21
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:09,880
- Nothing.
- Nothing.

22
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,040
Shut up!

23
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:12,160
One at a time.

24
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:13,880
You go first.

25
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,320
We… We're just…

26
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,960
- We're just part-timers.
- Part-timers.

27
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,480
Part-timers?

28
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:20,560
What kind of "part-timers"
walk around with tattoos

29
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:21,880
and carry stuff like that?

30
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:23,520
We don't know anything.

31
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:26,040
We just spent 200 yuan to get the tattoos,

32
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:27,960
so we could go collect debts.

33
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:29,400
You came here to collect money?

34
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:32,320
How much does the Xu family
owe Jin Manshan?

35
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:34,040
Two hundred and fifty thousand.

36
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,440
How much did they actually borrow?

37
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,320
Eight thousand.

38
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:44,240
You loan sharks are real math geniuses.

39
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:48,320
This isn't your first time here, is it?

40
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,440
Yesterday afternoon.

41
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,280
- Afternoon.
- We came yesterday afternoon.

42
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:56,280
DIE

43
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,200
Are you sure?

44
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:58,680
No one is home.

45
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:00,360
What's the point of writing that?

46
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:01,960
You're so clueless.

47
00:04:02,040 --> 00:04:04,040
I wrote this to show Mr. Jin.

48
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,320
Sling it over your shoulder. Quick.

49
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:25,120
DAJIANCHANG NEIGHBORHOOD

50
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,280
- I'm hungry.
- How about

51
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:29,960
we go grab something to eat?

52
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,480
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

53
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:45,920
- We went out to get some tofu pudding.
- We ate tofu pudding.

54
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,680
- Then we came back.
- We saw the tape had been removed.

55
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:49,960
- We thought the family had returned.
- We thought…

56
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,280
Enough.

57
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,600
Are you two performing crosstalk?

58
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:54,040
When was the last time

59
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,440
the father and daughter
were seen leaving home?

60
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:58,640
People said it was the day
before Hong Kong, China's handover.

61
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:00,080
Someone saw them leave,

62
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:02,160
- and they never came back.
- Never came back.

63
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:05,120
30TH, MONDAY

64
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,520
Why did the Xu family borrow money?

65
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:15,040
- Because…
- You answer.

66
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:16,800
The daughter was devoted.

67
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,360
She borrowed money to treat her father.

68
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:20,080
Her father was in poor health.

69
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:23,000
The medical bills
drained everything they had.

70
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:23,960
What illness?

71
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:25,600
No idea.

72
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,520
- We don't know.
- We really don't know.

73
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:33,520
We honestly don't know.

74
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:45,720
You were carrying a gun just now.

75
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,480
Did you file the paperwork to borrow it?

76
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:53,240
FOR DRAMATIC EFFECT. DO NOT IMITATE

77
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:54,360
What are you doing?

78
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,440
What are you doing exactly?

79
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:00,080
That's pure reflex.

80
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:02,960
When criminals hear a gunshot,
they assume it's real.

81
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:04,800
What?

82
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:07,400
Reflex.

83
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:10,160
A real cop using a fake fun?
And you're proud of it.

84
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,800
As long as it works.

85
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:13,480
You nearly scared me to death.

86
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:16,360
The Xu father and daughter
might've gone to relatives to dodge debt.

87
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:17,920
I want to check their household records.

88
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,040
Do you know what time it is?
The registry office isn't open yet.

89
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:23,280
Two more hours. I'll wait.

90
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:28,000
WEIYANG PUBLIC SECURITY

91
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:43,280
<i>You dressed like</i>
<i>some imperial envoy on tour.</i>

92
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,560
<i>Chasing suspects</i>
<i>in leather shoes and slacks?</i>

93
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:47,200
<i>That's not practical.</i>

94
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:28,280
Timing matters more than being early.

95
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,040
Oh my!

96
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:38,240
He Yuanhang, what happened to you?

97
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:41,560
Paint. I brushed against it.

98
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:43,400
Brushed against it?

99
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:46,600
Looks like you fell into a paint vat.

100
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:48,360
That's what being a detective is like.

101
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:50,240
Dirty, exhausting, and rough.

102
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:52,800
- You never know what tomorrow will bring.
- Go wash up.

103
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:55,840
Dad, you've changed.

104
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:59,000
Ever since you joined
the criminal department,

105
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:01,240
you've been talking big.

106
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:04,880
Kiddo, I promise you.

107
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,880
I'll prove it soon enough.

108
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:12,680
That hairstyle is cool.

109
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:15,320
When I grow up, I want one like that too.

110
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:28,440
MODERN LAW ENFORCEMENT
UNWAVERING POLICE EXCELLENCE

111
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:33,159
- Morning, Captain Zhao, Captain Qu.
- Morning.

112
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,039
Captain Zhao.

113
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:44,000
The case in Binchuan District,
where four teenagers had gone missing,

114
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:45,400
has been going on for almost two weeks.

115
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:47,000
We still haven't found them.

116
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:49,400
All kinds of rumors are spreading online,

117
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:51,360
and it's causing quite a stir.

118
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:52,800
- Director Zou mentioned…
- I know.

119
00:08:52,880 --> 00:08:54,280
He already called me.

120
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:56,360
We'll be assisting the municipal bureau
on this joint case.

121
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:59,520
- Qu. You take this case.
- Alright.

122
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:00,440
FAIR AND JUST, LOYAL AND TRUE

123
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:03,160
Contact all stations in our jurisdiction.
Get them involved too.

124
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,600
No problem.

125
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:05,880
We all know each other. They'll cooperate.

126
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,520
Report to me immediately
when there are any solid leads.

127
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,520
Understood, Captain Zhao.

128
00:09:09,640 --> 00:09:10,720
Captain Zhao.

129
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,840
- Good morning.
- Morning.

130
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:18,000
Captain Zhao, about the report
I submitted earlier,

131
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:20,160
when would you have time to approve it?

132
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,000
What report?

133
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:25,400
The application for field duty.

134
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:30,480
Xiaohe,

135
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:33,320
field work is tough,

136
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,920
exhausting, and dangerous.

137
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,560
Captain Zhao, I'm not afraid.

138
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:38,120
I studied criminal investigation
for six years.

139
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:39,560
Fieldwork is exactly what I'm trained for.

140
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,160
Oh, well.

141
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:48,080
If only you showed that same dedication

142
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:50,600
to taking care of your dad.

143
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:52,200
- Captain Zhao.
- But…

144
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:53,960
The report you requested is ready.

145
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,480
Come with me.

146
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:59,680
Does Han Zi'ang have a phone or a camera?

147
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:01,000
No.

148
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:04,040
There's not much to do at Yuanlongli.

149
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:06,440
People mostly go there
to take photos and videos.

150
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,480
If your child doesn't have
a phone or a camera,

151
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:09,480
it's unlikely he went there.

152
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:11,840
Here's what you do.
Go home and wait for now.

153
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,440
Maybe he skipped class
and went out to play.

154
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:15,200
That's impossible.

155
00:10:15,280 --> 00:10:16,960
I met a psychic this morning.

156
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:20,080
He said Ang must be in Yuanlongli.

157
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:22,480
A psychic? That's all nonsense.

158
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:24,240
Why would a psychic lie?

159
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:26,160
He promised to help me find my child.

160
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:29,520
Ma'am, what did this psychic look like?

161
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:30,800
He…

162
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,240
He is about this tall,

163
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:34,840
wearing a colored shirt,
and carrying a bag.

164
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:36,920
He said all the missing kids in Yuanlongli

165
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,240
were found by him.

166
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:44,400
Han Zi'ang.

167
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:46,960
Come out.

168
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:49,000
Your mom's looking for you.

169
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:53,560
Now that Yuanlongli
is about to be demolished,

170
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:57,320
everything hidden inside
will come out into the open.

171
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:04,360
DEMOLITION

172
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:20,280
You see,
if you hadn't gone to Beijing back then,

173
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,440
would things between you two…

174
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:23,720
No.

175
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:28,240
And there's no "if".

176
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,800
I've always wondered.

177
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,080
You two were such a good match.

178
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:37,560
What happened in the end?

179
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:16,320
Where did the trike go?

180
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:20,000
What trike?

181
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:21,920
Are you remembering it wrong?

182
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,400
No way.

183
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:27,000
It was blocking the door.
I moved it myself.

184
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,720
Someone must've been here.

185
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:38,960
- Let's go back and check.
- Sir.

186
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:27,360
MISSING PERSON

187
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:36,000
You're here.

188
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,400
What are you doing here?

189
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:44,800
What kind of question is that?
I'm here to work.

190
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:47,200
Did you track down
their household registration?

191
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,680
The Xu's have two relatives in Weiyang.

192
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:54,040
Xu Zhihong has a sister. Xu Meng
has an uncle on her mother's side.

193
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:55,800
XU MEIQIN'S AND QIAO GUOQIANG'S ADDRESSES

194
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:00,640
Let's split up. Make it quick.

195
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:08,800
I don't have a brother like that.
And no niece either.

196
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:15,080
Xu Meng borrowed money from you
to treat her father, right?

197
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:18,080
To be honest, in my brother's condition,

198
00:14:18,160 --> 00:14:19,680
he'd be better off dead.

199
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:20,800
It's done.

200
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:25,120
- Alright. Have a nice day.
- Thank you.

201
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:29,600
He couldn't pay the debt,
so he kept pestering me.

202
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:32,960
Look around. This place is a mess.

203
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:35,400
When was the last time you saw them?

204
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:37,880
Last year, one night.
He suddenly had an attack.

205
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:40,080
Meng brought him over to borrow money.

206
00:14:41,760 --> 00:14:43,040
Aunt.

207
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:46,160
Open the door, Aunt.

208
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:47,680
Aunt.

209
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:48,800
Aunt.

210
00:14:49,640 --> 00:14:52,520
- Meng.
- Aunt, my dad's sick again.

211
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:57,160
Slow down.

212
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:07,640
Aunt, could you…

213
00:15:18,040 --> 00:15:19,280
Thank you, Aunt.

214
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:21,880
Meng.

215
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:26,520
I'm planning to move away soon.

216
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:28,720
Where are you moving to?

217
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:42,600
I understand.

218
00:15:42,680 --> 00:15:44,560
I won't come again.

219
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:48,280
I'll find a way to pay you back.

220
00:15:56,560 --> 00:15:58,600
Take this. Go to the hospital now.

221
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:00,280
Thank you, Aunt.

222
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:13,920
She's a good kid.

223
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:16,880
Definitely.

224
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:19,240
What a shame.

225
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:21,680
She got dragged down by her father.

226
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:25,960
To be frank,

227
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:27,920
when I heard my brother had gone missing,

228
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:32,480
I actually felt relieved.

229
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:36,040
I shouldn't have felt that way.

230
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:40,960
Life and death aren't up to us.

231
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:43,080
Not up to us?

232
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:45,840
He brought this on himself.

233
00:16:45,920 --> 00:16:47,960
He was perfectly fine before.

234
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:48,880
But two summers ago,

235
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:51,160
he and his daughter
went to Mount Wu for a trip,

236
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:53,360
like they were possessed.

237
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:55,480
They ran into an accident
in the mountains.

238
00:16:55,560 --> 00:17:00,480
He fell off a cliff
and ended up like this.

239
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:02,960
Half dead.

240
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:05,880
A mountain accident?
The Mount Wu incident?

241
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:08,119
MAJOR MOUNTAIN ACCIDENT HIT MOUNT WU
KUNHAI CITY, YESTERDAY

242
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:10,319
It started with heavy rain,
then thick fog.

243
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:13,520
That tour group got lost
the moment they entered the mountains.

244
00:17:13,599 --> 00:17:15,079
You can imagine. In the mountains,

245
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:17,040
there was no food, no water,

246
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:18,839
and no one coming to help.

247
00:17:19,839 --> 00:17:21,599
Many people froze to death.

248
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:23,760
My uncle was one of the lucky ones.

249
00:17:23,839 --> 00:17:25,280
He made it out alive.

250
00:17:25,359 --> 00:17:26,599
He might as well be dead!

251
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:33,960
That's how Xu Zhihong
ended up with his condition.

252
00:17:37,520 --> 00:17:40,240
- Can I borrow this newspaper?
- Take that.

253
00:17:40,760 --> 00:17:42,240
Why are you keeping
that frigging paper anyway?

254
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:47,600
When was the last time you saw Xu Meng?

255
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,320
When?

256
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:51,240
Heaven knows how long ago!

257
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:56,520
Officer, want me to pour you some tea?

258
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:21,720
Does anyone in your family do this too?

259
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:24,120
No, I just like it.

260
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:31,960
Young man,

261
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:35,360
do you think people are afraid
of dying at the end?

262
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:40,040
I don't really know.

263
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:42,080
Look at my brother-in-law.

264
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:43,560
He can barely breathe.

265
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:45,200
Living like that is worse than dying.

266
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:47,920
So why keep him alive?

267
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,760
Last winter, I cut ties with them.

268
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:51,840
Just to keep him alive,

269
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:53,320
the father and daughter scammed people.

270
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:55,480
She even turned to prostitution
and worked as a hostess.

271
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:58,480
Anyone tied to relatives like that
is doomed.

272
00:18:58,560 --> 00:18:59,840
Don't talk about Meng like that.

273
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,040
Why not?

274
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:02,720
Didn't Xu Meng take advantage of you?

275
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:05,360
You lent her your wedding money.

276
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:07,400
She said she'd pay it back
right away. Did she?

277
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,880
And your engagement fell apart.

278
00:19:09,960 --> 00:19:11,320
You really don't know why?

279
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:28,560
Do you know if they crossed
the wrong people?

280
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:30,840
Probably loan sharks.

281
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:34,360
My uncle is actually a good man.

282
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,560
He raised Meng all by himself.

283
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:38,080
It wasn't easy.

284
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:41,720
So Xu Zhihong was a loving father?

285
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:43,720
Loving, you say? More like a "treasure".

286
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,800
He's in that state and still not dead.

287
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:47,200
I'd say he's some treasure indeed.

288
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:48,680
Dad!

289
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:54,520
MAJOR MOUNTAIN ACCIDENT HIT MOUNT WU
KUNHAI CITY, YESTERDAY

290
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:57,240
They survived an accident,
went into debt for treatment,

291
00:19:57,320 --> 00:19:58,960
and now someone hired a hit on them.

292
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:01,600
The Xu's really have it rough.

293
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:03,720
Let's just hope
nothing else happens to them.

294
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:07,720
Hard to say.

295
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:11,120
From the scene at their home,
they left in a hurry.

296
00:20:11,720 --> 00:20:14,360
But why would they go to Yuanlongli?

297
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:16,720
And then disappear in the elevator?

298
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:21,040
Something about this doesn't add up.

299
00:20:22,120 --> 00:20:23,360
Up till now,

300
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:25,640
we still don't know how they disappeared.

301
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:28,760
Let's hope nothing else happens to them.

302
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:30,640
Otherwise, this case
could drag on forever.

303
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:38,480
I'm heading to the video rental shop
Wolfie mentioned,

304
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:39,400
see if I can dig up anything

305
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:40,560
- about the person who hired the hit.
- Well.

306
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:42,720
I think we should start
with the loan shark.

307
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:44,880
Jin Manshan wasn't telling
the truth yesterday.

308
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:46,480
He was definitely holding something back.

309
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:48,440
We should press him
and get the truth out of him.

310
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:51,400
Then you go find Jin Manshan.
I'll check out the video rental shop.

311
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:54,440
That place is full of all kinds
of shady characters.

312
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:56,600
Don't scare them off.

313
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:10,080
Officer He.

314
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:12,000
Hm?

315
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:16,240
Actually, we can go together.

316
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:18,880
Better to have each other's backs.

317
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:23,320
That foot bath grossed you out that much?

318
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:27,680
Sure. Call me "sir", and I'll go with you.

319
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:33,240
He can't take a joke.

320
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:38,000
WANXIANG VIDEO RENTAL SHOP

321
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:40,840
CONTINUOUS SCREENINGS
NO ADDITIONAL TICKETS NEEDED

322
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:46,320
RAN FANGXU POLICE ID

323
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:03,920
Officers, this way, please.

324
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:05,800
SCREENING ROOM

325
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:08,560
TOP PICKS FROM HK
ACTION-PACKED WESTERNS

326
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:12,440
The night before last,

327
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:14,720
someone came in wearing a cap and a mask.

328
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:15,680
Ring a bell?

329
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:19,240
So many people come and go every day.

330
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:20,800
How would I remember?

331
00:22:21,320 --> 00:22:23,720
Jin Manlang was here too.
You don't remember that either?

332
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:25,200
I really don't know.

333
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:28,400
We wouldn't dare mess
with those gangsters.

334
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:29,840
You're lying.

335
00:22:29,920 --> 00:22:31,680
No way.

336
00:22:31,760 --> 00:22:34,160
How would I dare lie to you officers?

337
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:35,880
- You!
- Hey.

338
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:36,920
Ran.

339
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:38,160
Come over.

340
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:49,680
Nothing he says is true.

341
00:22:49,760 --> 00:22:51,720
He's just trying to get by.

342
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:53,960
Pushing him won't help.
Everyone's got their struggles.

343
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:01,440
This is a murder-for-hire case.

344
00:23:01,520 --> 00:23:02,800
Lives are on the line.

345
00:23:02,880 --> 00:23:05,720
If he won't cooperate,
I'll file for an investigation right now.

346
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:07,280
Wait.

347
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:09,400
Let me think.

348
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:11,880
I'll think of a way.

349
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:31,040
THE PLUM IN THE GOLDEN VASE

350
00:23:36,160 --> 00:23:37,120
This one looks interesting.

351
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:40,200
I'll take it back
and watch it at the station.

352
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:43,720
It talks about human desires.

353
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:44,880
- Officer.
- What is it?

354
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:48,160
Look at me. My head just cleared up.

355
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:51,440
I do remember that guy wearing a mask.

356
00:23:52,040 --> 00:23:53,040
What did he look like?

357
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:54,760
Black cap, white mask. Does that help?

358
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:59,440
- How tall?
- I was sitting down. Couldn't tell.

359
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:00,920
What was he watching?

360
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:03,800
That's the strange part.
He didn't watch anything.

361
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:04,920
He went straight to the back
after coming in.

362
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:06,000
He said he was looking for the restroom.

363
00:24:06,080 --> 00:24:09,640
Then he talked to Wolf for a bit,
took a phone call, and left.

364
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:11,520
How did he leave? Did he drive?

365
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:13,200
I was sitting over there. I didn't see.

366
00:24:13,280 --> 00:24:14,280
You'd better be honest.

367
00:24:14,360 --> 00:24:16,120
I'm really good at faces.

368
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:18,960
I really am.

369
00:24:22,640 --> 00:24:25,000
VIDEO RENTAL SHOP

370
00:24:35,880 --> 00:24:36,720
What's wrong?

371
00:24:37,760 --> 00:24:39,920
It won't help to worry.
Let's go find Jin Manshan.

372
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:41,880
Get in.

373
00:25:21,920 --> 00:25:23,000
Mister.

374
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:25,720
What is it?

375
00:25:31,120 --> 00:25:33,000
Please. What do you want?

376
00:25:33,080 --> 00:25:34,320
Relax.

377
00:25:35,680 --> 00:25:37,240
Just want to ask about someone.

378
00:25:37,320 --> 00:25:39,600
- Go on, please.
- Stay still.

379
00:25:51,480 --> 00:25:52,320
So many books.

380
00:25:53,560 --> 00:25:56,120
This is sold by weight.
We can get a good price for it.

381
00:26:10,840 --> 00:26:11,760
There's a ghost making noise.

382
00:26:17,360 --> 00:26:19,840
- Where?
- Over there.

383
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:54,360
See it?

384
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:58,400
You know, my memory's sharp.

385
00:26:59,240 --> 00:27:01,400
This is obviously
a drifters' resting spot.

386
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:03,240
That doesn't prove anything.

387
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:05,640
Why not?

388
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:08,440
These two wooden stools
were on the 18th floor just now.

389
00:27:14,160 --> 00:27:16,680
Which means someone's been tailing us.

390
00:27:16,760 --> 00:27:17,720
Help!

391
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:20,600
- Help!
- Help!

392
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:23,120
- Help!
- Help!

393
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:25,440
Don't come any closer!

394
00:27:26,080 --> 00:27:28,120
- Help…
- Help!

395
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:30,200
Help…

396
00:27:30,800 --> 00:27:31,720
Stop!

397
00:27:34,440 --> 00:27:36,480
Sir! Sir!

398
00:27:48,640 --> 00:27:49,600
Ang!

399
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:51,640
Ang!

400
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:53,840
Ang!

401
00:27:54,360 --> 00:27:55,920
Is he okay?

402
00:27:56,440 --> 00:27:58,680
Ms. Wang, let's send
the boy to the hospital first.

403
00:27:58,760 --> 00:28:00,120
Quick. Get in.

404
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:02,880
- What's going on with the victim?
- He's the suspect.

405
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:04,560
These two are the victims.

406
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:05,880
The kid attacked them with a knife.

407
00:28:05,960 --> 00:28:06,920
Good thing it was dull.

408
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:08,760
Have you seen my dad?

409
00:28:10,440 --> 00:28:11,440
NEW YORK BLOCK

410
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:14,320
- Dad, you're hurt too?
- Just a scratch. I'm fine.

411
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:17,800
Where's Fangxu? He was just here.

412
00:28:24,720 --> 00:28:27,200
- Mr. He, are you alright?
- Just superficial.

413
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:28,800
Xiaohe, take my car.

414
00:28:28,880 --> 00:28:30,040
Get your dad home to rest.

415
00:28:31,160 --> 00:28:32,560
I don't need you worrying about me.

416
00:28:33,360 --> 00:28:34,720
Who's worrying about you?

417
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:36,280
Captain Zhao is taking us to the scene.

418
00:28:36,360 --> 00:28:37,480
Stop wandering around here.

419
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:40,480
Jerk, I found the boy.

420
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:42,000
What? Are you trying to take the credit?

421
00:28:42,080 --> 00:28:43,680
- Dad.
- No wonder you're bald.

422
00:28:45,120 --> 00:28:47,280
Living off other people's work.

423
00:28:49,920 --> 00:28:50,920
Ran!

424
00:28:52,640 --> 00:28:53,480
Ran!

425
00:28:54,520 --> 00:28:57,200
- Get in.
- Alright.

426
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:00,640
Let's go.

427
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:33,720
Why are we here?

428
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:38,080
Isn't Jin Manshan's men
supposed to be at Jinsha Market?

429
00:29:39,440 --> 00:29:41,560
Being a beat officer takes skill.

430
00:29:41,640 --> 00:29:44,280
These 20 years weren't for nothing.

431
00:29:54,520 --> 00:29:57,000
LEIGONG STREET

432
00:30:03,240 --> 00:30:04,680
They've got a lookout.

433
00:30:09,360 --> 00:30:11,200
Play drunk. Can you do that?

434
00:30:19,200 --> 00:30:21,920
- I want more.
- Slow down.

435
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:24,880
- Another carton.
- Watch the step. Slow down.

436
00:30:24,960 --> 00:30:26,920
I can drink another carton of beer.

437
00:30:27,640 --> 00:30:28,680
Wait.

438
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:30,520
Why don't we just go in?

439
00:30:30,600 --> 00:30:31,440
Why make it so complicated?

440
00:30:32,040 --> 00:30:34,040
It's a small gambling den.

441
00:30:34,120 --> 00:30:36,160
I busted it before.

442
00:30:37,240 --> 00:30:39,320
This time, we'll just scare them a bit.

443
00:30:40,160 --> 00:30:42,440
- Slow down.
- I'm fine.

444
00:30:49,600 --> 00:30:51,200
His legs.

445
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:58,920
Right here.

446
00:31:03,840 --> 00:31:05,920
Why is it you again, Officer He?

447
00:31:06,880 --> 00:31:07,840
Cut the crap.

448
00:31:07,920 --> 00:31:09,080
Is Jin Manshan inside?

449
00:31:10,400 --> 00:31:11,280
How many people?

450
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:13,920
- Over 20.
- More than 20?

451
00:31:21,600 --> 00:31:22,440
Where are you going?

452
00:31:22,520 --> 00:31:23,560
Too many of them.

453
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:25,400
We can't just rush in.
I need to check the layout first.

454
00:31:36,880 --> 00:31:38,600
Business looks pretty good lately.

455
00:31:39,120 --> 00:31:40,160
That's all the bosses.

456
00:31:40,240 --> 00:31:43,040
I just watch the door and keep lookout.

457
00:31:43,120 --> 00:31:46,240
Officer He,
please don't tell Mr. Jin it's me.

458
00:31:46,320 --> 00:31:49,360
You've got some nerve
to bargain with me, huh?

459
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:50,800
If you have time, read a book.

460
00:31:50,880 --> 00:31:52,720
Or get a proper job in Guangzhou.

461
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:54,720
Stop hanging around with these people.

462
00:31:54,800 --> 00:31:56,960
- Got it?
- Got it, Officer He.

463
00:32:04,640 --> 00:32:05,560
Listen up.

464
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:08,160
When you go back in,
as soon as you hear a gunshot,

465
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:10,080
shout "police are coming" four more times.

466
00:32:10,160 --> 00:32:11,960
Then hide. Stay out of sight
for a few days.

467
00:32:12,040 --> 00:32:13,440
When you come out,
just say you got detained.

468
00:32:13,520 --> 00:32:14,880
Understand?

469
00:32:14,960 --> 00:32:16,840
Officer He, you brought a gun?

470
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:17,760
Mm.

471
00:32:17,840 --> 00:32:19,200
That's intense.

472
00:32:19,280 --> 00:32:21,200
Stop talking and move.

473
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:29,400
There's a trash bin by the back door.

474
00:32:29,480 --> 00:32:32,560
I'll wait there
and catch anyone who slips out.

475
00:32:32,640 --> 00:32:35,280
You're taking the lead today.
Can you handle it?

476
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:36,880
Don't just curry favor
with others all the time.

477
00:32:37,880 --> 00:32:40,440
If I hadn't carried his legs just now,
would you have handled it alone?

478
00:32:41,600 --> 00:32:43,200
Cut it out.

479
00:32:43,280 --> 00:32:45,160
Open fire when I'm in position.

480
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:49,480
- What now?
- I've never seen Jin Manshan.

481
00:32:49,560 --> 00:32:50,920
What does he look like?

482
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:54,480
Big gold chain around his neck.
Two gold teeth.

483
00:32:56,760 --> 00:32:58,440
Big gold chain. Gold teeth.

484
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:18,960
Police are here!

485
00:33:20,240 --> 00:33:22,920
Police are here! Police!

486
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:24,480
Police!

487
00:33:24,560 --> 00:33:26,520
Police are here!

488
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:45,040
- Police are coming!
- Police are coming!

489
00:33:45,120 --> 00:33:47,760
- Run quickly. Police are coming!
- Police are here!

490
00:33:47,840 --> 00:33:50,160
- Run!
- Run quickly!

491
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:51,560
Move it now!

492
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:53,600
<i>Big gold chain. Gold teeth.</i>

493
00:34:13,679 --> 00:34:14,719
Jin Manshan!

494
00:34:15,360 --> 00:34:17,080
Not me. You got the wrong person.

495
00:34:28,280 --> 00:34:29,920
Police! Stay put!

496
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:34,800
Stop running! Stand right there!

497
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:50,040
Jin Manshan, stop!

498
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:52,320
He Yuanhang! He Yuanhang!

499
00:34:53,840 --> 00:34:55,159
He Yuanhang!

500
00:35:00,480 --> 00:35:01,600
Stop running!

501
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:14,800
Officer He, what is this?

502
00:35:14,880 --> 00:35:16,160
Why are you doing this?

503
00:35:16,240 --> 00:35:18,680
Also, what if the lamp post
leaks electricity?

504
00:35:18,760 --> 00:35:19,800
Cut the nonsense.

505
00:35:19,880 --> 00:35:21,800
Don't tell me you have no idea
why you're being cuffed.

506
00:35:21,880 --> 00:35:24,240
Yesterday afternoon,
when I asked about Xu Meng,

507
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:25,440
why didn't you say anything?

508
00:35:25,520 --> 00:35:29,240
Officer He, I don't follow.

509
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:30,680
Who is Xu Meng?

510
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:32,520
She borrowed 8,000 from you.

511
00:35:32,600 --> 00:35:34,320
It has grown to 250,000 with interest.

512
00:35:34,400 --> 00:35:36,040
Does that jog your memory?

513
00:35:36,120 --> 00:35:37,520
I've got a lot of borrowers.

514
00:35:38,120 --> 00:35:40,720
I don't remember small fry like that.

515
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:43,520
I only deal with big clients.

516
00:35:43,600 --> 00:35:45,040
Then why did you have
someone watching her house?

517
00:35:45,120 --> 00:35:48,000
Young man, you're really confusing me.

518
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:50,320
I don't even know if Xu Meng
is a man or a woman.

519
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:52,160
Why would I have someone watch her?

520
00:35:57,760 --> 00:36:00,120
Here. Take a look. Recognize this?

521
00:36:02,040 --> 00:36:04,120
I really have no idea.

522
00:36:04,200 --> 00:36:07,640
My guys handle small loans like 8,000.

523
00:36:08,440 --> 00:36:11,840
This wrench owes me money
and still runs off.

524
00:36:14,160 --> 00:36:15,760
Watch your mouth.

525
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:17,440
She owes money and skips out.

526
00:36:17,520 --> 00:36:19,600
Why should I respect her?
Did she respect me?

527
00:36:19,680 --> 00:36:20,560
It's not even 10,000.

528
00:36:20,640 --> 00:36:23,240
She could've paid it back somehow.

529
00:36:23,320 --> 00:36:26,840
- Wrench. I'll catch her one day…
- Can't you talk without swearing?

530
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:28,040
Huh?

531
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:30,520
There you go again.

532
00:36:37,600 --> 00:36:38,600
You!

533
00:36:39,760 --> 00:36:42,600
Officer He, you're done asking.

534
00:36:42,680 --> 00:36:44,000
Let me ask you something.

535
00:36:46,120 --> 00:36:49,320
What did Jin Manlang do?

536
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:51,120
Are you sure you don't know?

537
00:36:53,560 --> 00:36:56,680
Did that idiot run his mouth,
saying he killed someone?

538
00:36:57,400 --> 00:36:58,480
Don't believe him.

539
00:36:58,560 --> 00:37:00,440
He's been a coward since he was a kid.

540
00:37:00,520 --> 00:37:02,600
Too scared to kill a chicken,
and he talks about murder?

541
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:04,280
He's just bluffing.

542
00:37:06,320 --> 00:37:08,000
You don't know your brother very well.

543
00:37:16,520 --> 00:37:17,640
Jin Manshan,

544
00:37:17,720 --> 00:37:19,520
you assaulted a police officer.

545
00:37:19,600 --> 00:37:21,240
I could detain you for that.

546
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:23,160
But listen.

547
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:27,280
If you can help me find out
what else the father and daughter

548
00:37:27,360 --> 00:37:29,680
were involved in,
besides borrowing from you,

549
00:37:29,760 --> 00:37:31,760
we'll count it as making up for it.

550
00:37:31,840 --> 00:37:33,200
Do you get what I mean?

551
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:34,760
Yes.

552
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:43,360
- Thank you.
- Hands.

553
00:37:44,680 --> 00:37:45,680
Don't forget that.

554
00:38:06,120 --> 00:38:07,280
Where are we going?

555
00:38:08,480 --> 00:38:09,760
I'll drop you back at the dorm.

556
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:12,720
Let me off at a bus stop.

557
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:16,200
It's late. There are no buses now.

558
00:38:22,240 --> 00:38:24,680
I've noticed you've been off today.

559
00:38:25,600 --> 00:38:27,520
I told you. Lack of sleep can mess you up.

560
00:38:27,600 --> 00:38:28,920
You never listen.

561
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:31,640
Not enough sleep affects your judgment

562
00:38:31,720 --> 00:38:33,080
and makes you irritable.

563
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:36,280
He was being disrespectful.
He had it coming.

564
00:38:49,560 --> 00:38:52,080
Pass me the stuff in the door handle.

565
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:01,480
Stay-awake kit.

566
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:04,000
My daughter got it for me.

567
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:10,640
Your daughter sounds thoughtful.

568
00:39:11,680 --> 00:39:13,200
More than that.

569
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:14,720
Want to try?

570
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:26,120
Her teachers all say

571
00:39:26,640 --> 00:39:28,920
she takes after me.

572
00:39:29,680 --> 00:39:31,280
Quick-witted.

573
00:39:31,360 --> 00:39:33,600
The only problem is she's a bit stubborn.

574
00:39:34,280 --> 00:39:35,800
She's great at sports

575
00:39:35,880 --> 00:39:37,640
and loves figuring things out.

576
00:39:37,720 --> 00:39:38,880
Brains and brawn.

577
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:40,480
Just like me.

578
00:39:41,360 --> 00:39:44,560
Do you think I should
let her join the police like me,

579
00:39:44,640 --> 00:39:47,040
or go into finance like her mom?

580
00:39:47,720 --> 00:39:49,240
Don't mind me talking so much.

581
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:51,120
I'm driving at night.

582
00:39:51,200 --> 00:39:52,880
Talking keeps me awake.

583
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:56,360
It's fine. Go on.

584
00:39:56,440 --> 00:39:59,280
Don't let me do the talking.
You say something too.

585
00:40:01,720 --> 00:40:03,120
Why did you come to Weiyang?

586
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:05,440
My mom got married. I came with her.

587
00:40:07,160 --> 00:40:09,640
Right. You didn't finish
your story last time.

588
00:40:10,160 --> 00:40:12,320
What about you? What does your family do?

589
00:40:19,880 --> 00:40:21,480
Had a falling-out with them?

590
00:40:23,720 --> 00:40:27,080
You young people live so far from home.

591
00:40:27,840 --> 00:40:30,520
Your parents worry and nag a little.

592
00:40:30,600 --> 00:40:32,280
That's normal.

593
00:40:34,920 --> 00:40:36,240
They passed away.

594
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:24,880
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

595
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:31,000
Speak up.

596
00:41:31,080 --> 00:41:34,080
Mr. Jin, we were thinking
of staking out her place

597
00:41:34,160 --> 00:41:35,400
and handling it ourselves.

598
00:41:35,480 --> 00:41:36,520
Handling it yourselves?

599
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:38,520
So, your solution

600
00:41:38,600 --> 00:41:41,840
is to let the police trace it back to me?

601
00:41:42,680 --> 00:41:43,720
- No. It's not like that.
- Mr. Jin.

602
00:41:43,800 --> 00:41:45,360
Mr. Jin. Mr. Jin.

603
00:41:46,720 --> 00:41:48,280
Mr. Jin, I brought him here.

604
00:41:48,360 --> 00:41:49,840
Morning, Mr. Jin.

605
00:41:50,840 --> 00:41:51,880
Get lost.

606
00:41:54,160 --> 00:41:55,200
Thank you.

607
00:41:55,280 --> 00:41:56,720
- Sit.
- Let's sit.

608
00:41:59,040 --> 00:42:01,680
What is the situation inside?
What did he say?

609
00:42:01,760 --> 00:42:03,920
Wolf is doing fine in there.
Food is decent.

610
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:06,640
When he first got locked up,
he was bragging.

611
00:42:06,720 --> 00:42:07,600
He said he took out two people.

612
00:42:10,200 --> 00:42:12,720
How do you know he was bluffing?

613
00:42:12,800 --> 00:42:15,360
Mr. Jin, you know my nickname.

614
00:42:15,440 --> 00:42:16,480
Sharp Ears.

615
00:42:16,560 --> 00:42:19,480
When he first went in,
he clung to the bars and refused to move.

616
00:42:19,560 --> 00:42:21,240
He kept crying and told the warden

617
00:42:21,320 --> 00:42:22,880
that he didn't kill anyone.

618
00:42:22,960 --> 00:42:24,440
He only slaughtered a few chickens.

619
00:42:25,160 --> 00:42:26,000
Are you sure?

620
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:28,440
Mr. Jin, I was locked up
for pickpocketing.

621
00:42:28,520 --> 00:42:30,600
If Wolf had killed someone,
he wouldn't be in the same place as me.

622
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:36,360
You know the law pretty well.

623
00:42:37,240 --> 00:42:38,360
Thank you, Mr. Jin.

624
00:42:39,160 --> 00:42:40,080
By the way,

625
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:42,520
the one who hired him,

626
00:42:44,240 --> 00:42:45,080
any news?

627
00:42:45,160 --> 00:42:47,240
Mr. Jin, I've sent people
to track him down.

628
00:42:49,680 --> 00:42:51,240
That dickhead.

629
00:42:53,240 --> 00:42:55,040
He set Manlang up.

630
00:42:55,720 --> 00:42:56,880
I'll make sure he pays for it.

631
00:42:56,960 --> 00:42:58,400
Yeah. Make him pay.

632
00:42:59,400 --> 00:43:00,240
Mr. Jin.

633
00:43:02,360 --> 00:43:03,400
What is it?

634
00:43:04,680 --> 00:43:06,560
The punk who set Wolf up

635
00:43:06,640 --> 00:43:07,680
has been found.

636
00:43:09,080 --> 00:43:10,040
Who is it?

637
00:43:10,120 --> 00:43:12,720
The video rental shop owner
didn't recognize him,

638
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:13,840
but he remembers the car.

639
00:43:14,440 --> 00:43:16,880
A Mercedes. Plate ending in 688.

640
00:43:19,200 --> 00:43:20,760
688.

641
00:45:04,280 --> 00:45:07,960
PARKING GARAGE EXIT
